comment: Great bang for the buck. Cherry, sweet oak and brown sugar.
Light, cherry taste. Not bad for $15.

Had it with a sphere.
Nice, light and smooth with a mild kick.
Pretty good for the price. Taste of bananas, as certain whiskeys tend to do.
Very good for the price, taste of bananas slightly like whiskeys tend to do.

Nose- Pepper and sweet tea 
Body- This is a spicy one with black pepper, a bit of cinnamon, and a cherry note. 
Finish- Herein lies the rub. The dark pit fruit which I like gives way to a bitter aftertaste that I don’t care for.
It's Bourbon. Not horrible, not great, it just is. Thin, not very complex, short finish, decent mixed with cola. Many worse things out there at a higher cost.

Nose: cleaner, cherry and vanilla, a tiny bit of spice

Palate: super sweet at first and then opens up to some spice and heavy caramel. Very very light and sweet though

Finish: light, thin, and no burn and short
One of my favorite budget bourbons. Am I the only one who gets banana on the nose?

I'm not much of an expert but this one tastes a little............ different........ than other bourbons I've tried. I like it a lot. A little hard to find lately, but it's very cheap and pretty damn smooth. $23 for 1750 ml
Decent. Not a huge wheated fan but cannot complain too much over $17
